Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were
3 inches long and 1⁄3 inch thick).

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; lay flat and cut into
½-inch-thick sticks.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Lay tortillas on a clean
work surface.

Evenly spread @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} over tortillas. Arrange
1-2 @sliced turkey breast{8%ounce} slices in a single layer on each tortilla.

> We sent more turkey! Use as many or as few slices as you like.

Top with cucumber sticks.

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create
roll-ups. Halve roll-ups.

To serve: Serve turkey roll-ups with carrot sticks, apple
slices, @hummus{4%tablespoon}, @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, and
@honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} on the side.

> To stash: Refrigerate turkey roll-ups, carrot sticks, apple
slices, hummus, ranch dressing, and honey Dijon dressing
in separate containers and pack as desired.